column4: yo! I have a AMD phenom x3 cpu, is it considered i686, x86-64 or "dual architecture? (sry if this is a very common question)
type in a terminal: cat /proc/cpuinfo | grep lm    ..if you get any results then it is 64bit.
i didnt get any "results". So it's a 32 bits system. So what type of cpu is it? (i686, x86-64 or "dual architecture)
